 <para id="import-auto-id1915666">An athlete crosses a 25-m-wide river by swimming perpendicular to the water current at a speed of 0.5 m/s relative to the water. He reaches the opposite side at a distance 40 m downstream from his starting point. How fast is the water in the river flowing with respect to the ground? What is the speed of the swimmer with respect to a friend at rest on the ground?</para></problem></exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id2040310" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2040311">
<para id="import-auto-id1915676">A ship sailing in the Gulf Stream is heading <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>25.0º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"25.0"º} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> west of north at a speed of 4.00 m/s relative to the water. Its velocity relative to the Earth is <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>4.80 m/s</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{4 "." "80 m/s"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics>
