<para id="import-auto-id1915696">An ice hockey player is moving at 8.00 m/s when he hits the puck toward the goal. The speed of the puck relative to the player is 29.0 m/s. The line between the center of the goal and the player makes a <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>90.0º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"90.0º"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> angle relative to his path as shown in <link target-id="import-auto-id1829266"/>. What angle must the puck’s velocity make relative to the player (in his frame of reference) to hit the center of the goal?</para><para id="import-auto-id1916696">
