<para id="import-auto-id1888524"><emphasis>Unreasonable Results</emphasis> A commercial airplane has an air speed of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>280 m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"280 m/s"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> due east and flies with a strong tailwind. It travels 3000 km in a direction <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>5º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{5°} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> south of east in 1.50 h. (a) What was the velocity of the plane relative to the ground? (b) Calculate the magnitude and direction of the tailwind’s velocity. (c) What is unreasonable about both of these velocities? (d) Which premise is unreasonable?</para></problem></exercise>
